{%- comment -%}
  Patch Maker — single sign-on link for logged-in Shopify customers.

  WHAT IT DOES
    Mints a short-lived HMAC-SHA256 signed token from the storefront
    and renders a link to the Patch Maker's /sso route. The token
    carries the customer's id + email + expiry; the app verifies it
    against the same shared SHOPIFY_SSO_SECRET and starts a session
    so the customer's uploaded shapes / materials follow them.

    No token == bounce to the storefront login page (so unfamiliar
    customers don't see a half-broken "Sign in" button).

  CONFIGURE THESE TWO VALUES BEFORE USE
    - patch_maker_url   Public origin of your Patch Maker deploy.
                        No trailing slash. Example:
                        https://anypatch.coldesi.com
    - sso_secret        The SAME random string set as
                        SHOPIFY_SSO_SECRET on the Patch Maker host.
                        TREAT THIS LIKE A PASSWORD — anyone with it
                        can mint tokens for any customer. Use at
                        least 32 random bytes; rotate if leaked.

    Both values are HARDCODED into the snippet on purpose. Liquid
    has no concept of "private settings", so any value here ends up
    in the rendered HTML the moment the theme runs. The HMAC secret
    itself is consumed by the `hmac_sha256` filter and is NOT echoed
    into the markup — only the signed token is. Keep the snippet
    file out of any public theme repo.

  WHERE TO RENDER
    Anywhere a logged-in customer might want to design a patch:
      - top nav: "Design a custom patch" link
      - account page: "My uploaded shapes & materials"
      - product page (in addition to the cart-flow button)

      {%- render 'sso_link',
            label: 'Design a custom patch',
            next:  '/' -%}

    `label` is the link text (defaults to "Design your patch").
    `next` is the path inside the Patch Maker to land on after
    SSO redeem; must start with `/` for safety (the server
    refuses any other value).

  SECURITY NOTES
    - Tokens are valid for 5 minutes — short enough that a leaked
      URL is mostly harmless, long enough for one redirect hop.
    - The token includes the customer's email but NEVER any
      password, address, or order data. The Patch Maker uses it
      only for display + scoping uploads.
    - If a customer is not logged in, we render a link to the
      storefront login page with a redirect param so they come
      back here after signing in — the snippet then mints the
      token on the next request.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign patch_maker_url = 'https://pm.octopatches.com' -%}
{%- assign sso_secret = '84e309e6e7c52f8289354dd9961ba4261cb3c4a839470fa7fe15c2c80cf96a35' -%}

{%- assign sso_label = label | default: 'Design your patch' -%}
{%- assign sso_next  = next  | default: '/' -%}

{%- if customer -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    Build the payload bytes EXACTLY the way shopify.make_sso_token()
    does on the Python side: sort keys, no whitespace, id as string.
    Liquid's `json` filter handles email escaping (quotes, control
    chars). Do not insert spaces — they'd change the HMAC input.

    Token lifetime: 5 minutes. Matches the Python default
    (make_sso_token's ttl_seconds=300) and is long enough for the
    redirect hop without giving a leaked URL a long replay window.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign now_ts = 'now' | date: '%s' | plus: 0 -%}
  {%- assign exp_ts = now_ts | plus: 300 -%}
  {%- capture sso_body -%}{"email":{{ customer.email | downcase | json }},"exp":{{ exp_ts }},"id":"{{ customer.id }}"}{%- endcapture -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    base64url-encode the body. Shopify's base64_encode uses standard
    +/ alphabet with padding; the Patch Maker decoder accepts both
    standard AND url-safe encodings, so the replace-and-strip below
    is a polish step (no plus / slash in URLs) rather than a hard
    requirement. Padding strip is safe either way: the decoder
    re-pads internally.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign sso_body_b64 = sso_body
        | base64_encode
        | replace: '+', '-'
        | replace: '/', '_'
        | replace: '=', '' -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    hmac_sha256 returns the digest as lowercase hex. The Patch
    Maker decoder accepts EITHER hex or base64url for the sig
    field, so we ship the hex here (no further conversion needed).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign sso_sig_hex = sso_body | hmac_sha256: sso_secret -%}

  {%- assign sso_token = sso_body_b64 | append: '.' | append: sso_sig_hex -%}
  {%- assign sso_next_encoded = sso_next | url_encode -%}
  {%- assign sso_href = patch_maker_url
      | append: '/sso?token='
      | append: sso_token
      | append: '&next='
      | append: sso_next_encoded -%}

  <a class="patch-maker-sso" href="{{ sso_href }}" rel="noopener">
    {{ sso_label }}
  </a>
{%- else -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    Logged-out fallback: nudge them to sign in first. Set
    return_to so the customer lands back on this page (where the
    snippet will then mint the token).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <a class="patch-maker-sso patch-maker-sso--signin"
     href="{{ routes.account_login_url }}?return_to={{ request.path | url_encode }}">
    Sign in to {{ sso_label | downcase }}
  </a>
{%- endif -%}

<style>
  .patch-maker-sso {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background: #1f2937;
    color: #fff !important;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: background 120ms ease-in-out;
  }
  .patch-maker-sso:hover { background: #111827; }
  .patch-maker-sso--signin { background: #6b7280; }
  .patch-maker-sso--signin:hover { background: #4b5563; }
</style>
